11/03/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prosecutors filed charges Wednesday (March 10th) against three former Bosnian army members for war crimes committed against civilians and prisoners of war in the village of Trusina, in 1993.
Mensur Memic, Dzevad Salcin and Senad Hakalovic allegedly participated in an attack that left 18 civilians and four soldiers dead, and four people wounded.
(B92, Beta, BHRT - 10/03/10)
